Why don't eggs share information? Because they'd break each other's confidentiality! But seriously, I once asked my sandwich if it wanted to hear a fact, but it was too filled to process. Then my salad chimed in, saying it was too fresh to understand anything complex. So I turned to my soup, but it was too busy simmering with thoughts! Moral of the story: Food has a capacity for knowledge, but sometimes it's just too deliciously occupied to show it!